body:
Like this old issue #659

for this code

```
`ifndef __ADDX__
 `define __ADDX__

 `include "src/alu/arithm/add.v"

module addX (a, b, cin, out, cout);
   parameter WIRE = 8;

   input [WIRE-1:0] a, b;
   input            cin;

   output [WIRE-1:0] out;
   output            cout;

   wire              ret;

   if (WIRE > 1)
     begin
        add add0 (a[0], b[0], cin, out[0], ret);
        addX #(.WIRE(WIRE-1)) recall(a[WIRE-1:1],
                                     b[WIRE-1:1],
                                     ret,
                                     out[WIRE-1:1],
                                     cout);
     end
   else
     add add0 (a[0], b[0], cin, out[0], cout);

endmodule

`endif
```

you can see here, verilator define WIRE=3 but instantiate only 1 "add" cell.
